The paper deals with Bayesian networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The concepts of monotonicity and stochastic dominance are also commonly used in statistical learning theory (cs.LG). The problem of determining whether a network is monotone in distribution is a computational complexity problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The application of the algorithm to a real-life network in oncology suggests a potential application in the field of medical informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with probability distributions and information theory, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
